First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden are celebrating the first anniversary of their initiative, Joining Forces, which aims to support military families. They will embark on a two-day tour visiting various cities, including Philadelphia, Shreveport, and Jacksonville. The tour will highlight organizations and companies that have made significant commitments to support military families. The initiative focuses on employment, education, and wellness for veterans and military families. The tour will include an anniversary celebration at the White House, an announcement of a major nursing initiative in Philadelphia, an appearance on The Colbert Report in New York City, an announcement of the 50,000th hire through Joining Forces in Shreveport, and a celebration honoring young women from military families in Jacksonville.